HEADWORD: Winterly
<hw>Win"ter*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like winter; wintry; cold;
hence, disagreeable, cheerless; <as>as, <ex>winterly</ex>
news</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sir growing more <qex>winterly</qex> in the month of
April.</q> <rj><qau>Camden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Winter-proud</ent>⟦br⟧
